titute SURI  etc  The results of this research are presented in the form of both posters  informal demonstrations  or papers  more formal short lectures  as part of a special day of events  Cadets also have an opportunity to highlight alternative work  such as internships  experiential learning and service projects  In addition  you may propose a panel about a topic of your choice or propose workshops of interest to you  The Spring Symposium will be held across Post on Thursday  April 21  2016  Abstract submission is extended to CAD Tuesday  March 15  Accepted abstracts can expect notification on March 30  2016  All are welcome to attend  Questions should be sent to MAJ Josh Iddings  iddingsjg vmi edu V CUR Program Coordinator  V CUR s Symposium is supported in part by the Jackson Hope Fund  Abstract Submission Preparing an Abstract Preparing a Poster Presentation Preparing an Oral Presentation VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 